column2: High algae content- level tied to dam
Ice out on 4/5/1987- and water dirty and turbulent- May be turning over.
Water too low to read gauge
Gauge in mud- high algae content
Hot weather- 80 - 88 degrees during the past week.  Temp is 76 degrees.
Water temperature at 6" deep is 58 degrees.
Green slime on top and mixed into water
Recent rains of 7" or more- sent bogs floating- water dirty- lake should be dredged out
Lake level brought down by Department of Natural Resources. More weeds than ever. Fishing poor.
Low lake level- Department of Natural Resources directive- has affected spawning and fishing.
Heavy green slime near shores.  Clumps of rotting plant life in water.  Department of Natural Resources lowering the lake level is no help to water quality.
Sunny day- slight chop on water- no rain lately- lake level still being held low for dam inspection- a 3 month job it seems!
2.84" of rain since last reading- algae on surface.
Sunny- several inches of rain since last reading- water temp 59.
3.43" of rain since last reading.  Typical summer bloom coming on.
Lake starting in its bloom time- no rain for about a week- windy day- sunny skies.
Wading near shore is undesirable- scum is on top- out in the middle it is okay in some areas.  The lake is still being kept too low by your dam division.
Recent rains- lake vegetation is rotting and dying.  Sunny day with strong wind from the south west.
2 weeks since ice off- lake still low- high winds for 2 days- 2 days ago.
Weeds starting to appear-has been windy-nice sunny day breeze from se.
Public perception also due to floating brown muck.  Hazy sunny day-no rain lately.  Lots of blooming-weed growth.  Lake is too low!
Slightly overcast day - rain 2 days ago- ugly blobs of goop floating on weeds by shore lake.  2' less clarity than 2 weeks ago.
Lake very low-muck along shore + in weed line.
Lake low-full of floating scum + hairy like black blobs of stuff.  Lake looks like a sewer holding area.
Lake level is still low- snot balls floating all over- shoreline is full of mucky crap.
No rain for a week- 3 days ago the surface looked like green paint- with gobs of gook floating about - much better today.
Color of water is brown but translucent- light frost 2 weeks ago.
Two days of rain just before reading date.
Lots of dead fish in weeds-lake water not too inviting.
Lots of rain-need a better spot for lake gauge.
Ice out two weeks ago on southern end and 2 days  later on north end.
As bad as it can get.
Strange slime all over lake and lots of balls of "junk" all floating over lake
3 days of light rain- lake has scum on surface here + there.
Water is best i've ever seen it in a long while.
Water back to it's usual murkiness.
Rained overnight. partly cloudy. clearest I have ever seen the lake.
Overcast- rain off and on. gunk floating around.
Rain 2 days ago- lake is up.
Pea soup. This lake needs help. It is a pretty little lake- but it gets SO gunky and rubbery stuff even forms on the boat and motor and it needs to be scraped off.
lake is pretty good right now
lake is low- no rain- very green
Partly cloudy.  Approximately 70 degrees F.  south wind.   Water is murky and green.
Saturday of Memorial weekend.  Partly cloudy-bright- windy.  Lake not busy--3 or 4 boats on lake only.  No floating particles in water.

Did secchi reading only.  Bright day- partly cloudy.  Saw a lone loon on the lake.  It was preening and cleaning itself.  Entertained us for about half an hour.  Lake was quiet with a few fishing boats.
Nice day- mostly sunny 78 degrees-light breeze. Little activity on the lake. Heavy rain shower yesterday.
Totally sunny day. very nice. a little breezy- normal activity on the lake- not busy- a few boats
Clear sunny day- a little windy.  Water has green particles in it- but fairly clear. Saw our lone loon in Kasal Bay.
In the evening.  Partly cloudy- quiet + calm.  Green particles in the water.
A beautiful- sunny Sunday morning.  Light winds- partly cloudy.  Water has lots of green particles suspended in it.
Partly cloudy Saturday morning.  Chilly with some wind.
Little green around shoreline- weeds are visible- south breeze- sunshine- 68 to 70 degrees
Partly cloudy day. Light breeze. Nice spring day.  Approx. 60 degrees Fahrenheit.
Clear to partly cloudy with light breeze.  Trees just budding out.  A nice spring day.
Out for a pontoon ride and stopped to take a secchi disk reading.
Partly cloudy.  Spotty rain showers and downpours- windy. Partly cloudy.  Spotty rain showers and downpours- windy.
Beautiful sunny day with a light breeze.
Probe broken and mailed in for repair - used research station probe
Sunny and calm.  Saw beaver swimming in the narrows of the lake.

column1: Katelin Anderson with Polk County and her helper were with us in the pontoon.

column2: probe out of battery- out w/Roger and Vicki
Nice early spring day.  Mostly sunny- cool and slightly windy.
Cool sunny spring day.  Clear sky with light wind. Cool sunny spring day.  Clear sky with light wind.
Cool + breezy.  Difficult to keep pontoon in place.  Partly cloudy.  Memorial Day weekend.
Beautiful sunny day.  A little cool---mid 60's.  Light breeze.  No one else on the lake.
Mostly cloudy and breezy.  A bit humid.

Seeing many dead crappies on the lake started over the weekend.  So went out to check temps- etc.  Called DNR to report dead fish.  Someone is coming to check.  We are collecting samples of fish that are dying or just dead for DNR to look at when they come.
Rained earlier but now partly cloudy. Cool---66 degrees.  Has been cool for the last week.
Nice sunny day with light breeze out of the west. Nice sunny day with light breeze out of the west.

Beautiful spring morning with clear skies.  Lake is like a mirror. Hazy sunshine + humid today.  Will be in the 90's today. Hazy sunshine + humid.  Will be in the 90's today.   Hazy sunshine + humid.  Will be in the 90's today. Hazy sunshine + humid.    hazy sunshine- hot and humid day Cloudy and rainy- breezy and cool. Cloudy and rainy- breezy and cool. Cloudy and rainy- breezy and cool. Cloudy- rainy and cool.
Nice evening. Calm winds. Water is green with a lot of floating scum in the lake.
Partly cloudy with light breeze.  Beautiful day!  Saw eagle sitting on the sandbar.
Secchi reading taken by LEAPS on all four trade lakes
Cool temps- light wind. Rainy earlier but now clearing skies and sunny. Cool temps- light wind. Rainy earlier but now clearing skies and sunny.
Cool and cloudy- rained .8" yesterday.  Saw beaver swimming along shoreline.
Cloudy to partly cloudy.  Jack and Mona LaMont were with us.
Partly cloudy. Beautiful day after bad storms over last two days with rain and wind.
Mostly cloudy and chilly.  Rained about an inch yesterday afternoon.
Cloudy and light rain.  Rained 2.37 inches overnight + early morning.  Breezy. Cloudy and light rain.  Rained 2.37 inches overnight + early morning.  Breezy.
Nice day.  Partly cloudy and cool---about 65 degrees F.
A beautiful summer day---bright and sunny.  A lot of people enjoying the lake.  Our shoreline is gross with algae but middle of lake is great.
Very warm- humid day.  Got 1.13 inches of rain overnight and in early morning.  Getting sunny now.
Gorgeous day!  Completely clear and slightly cool.  Lake water is as clear as it ever gets---especially in late summer.  Low humidity.  No scum in lake.
Cool day.  Very cloudy with a light breeze.
